The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Kochi, Aug. 5: The Centre, in a warning to the 22 closed tea gardens in Kerala and Bengal, said if they were not reopened within a month, they would face a takeover risk. We have given one months time to the owners, beginning August 4 in Kerala and July 30 in Bengal. If they are not opened, Section 16 (E) of the Tea Act, 1953, will be invoked, the Union minister of state for commerce Jairam Ramesh said here today.

 New Delhi, Aug. 5: India is likely to sign an agreement with Switzerland on intellectual property rights to improve bilateral economic cooperation. The pact may be signed during the visit of Swiss federal counsellor and minister of economic affairs Doris Leuthard.

 Mumbai, Aug. 5: The National Commodity amp; Derivatives Exchange (NCDEX) has asked its members to maintain their minimum net worth requirement at Rs 50 lakh, failing which the exchange will block an amount based on the size of deficiency in the minimum net worth.

 New Delhi, Aug. 5: Ficci has suggested setting up an independent regulatory authority, coupled with efficient arbitration mechanism, to ensure speedy development of road and highway network in the country.

 New Delhi, Aug. 5: Reliance Communications will launch a service that will enable users to send money orders through their handsets. The company is exploring financial tieups with financial institutions for the service.




